text: Coregonus lutokka is a species of ray-finned fish in the genus Coregonus. Its native habitat is Lake Onega and Lake Ladoga, although it has been introduced to many other water bodies in Russia. It eats larvae, molluscs and crustaceans, but in the summer, it goes to the top and feeds on zooplankton. ==References== Category:Fish of Russia Category:Coregonus
